obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (72814)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Transfers of property by and to the Agent to the Governor General in Council, and institution of legal proceedings by him.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_188814_1675765637561&sectionId=72814&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_188814_1675765637561
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Governor General in Council, the person for`
  line `the time being holding the office of Agent to the Governor General in Council for the Affairs of the late`
  line `King of Oudh and for the Purposes of Act XIX of 1887, may—`
  line
  line `(a) in his own name and by his name of office dispose of any moveable and immoveable property`
  line `of His late Majesty the King of Oudh in as full and effectual a manner as His Majesty could have`
  line `disposed of it in his lifetime;`
  line
  line `(b) by his name of office take a conveyance of any moveable or immoveable property in which His`
  line `late Majesty had a beneficial interest; and`
  line
  line `(c) by his name of office institute any suit or other proceeding in any Civil, Criminal or Revenue`
  line `Court in connection with the possession of any moveable or immoveable property belonging to the`
  line `estate of His late Majesty or the dispossession of any person of any such property, or the recovery of`
  line `rents, debts or other moneys due to the estate, or otherwise in connection with the administration of the`
  line estate.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (72815)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Consequences ensuring on death, resignation or removal Agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_188814_1675765637561&sectionId=72815&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00120_188814_1675765637561
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `On the departure from British`
  line `India, or the death, resignation or removal, of an Agent to the Governor General for the Affairs and Purposes`
  line `aforesaid, the following consequences shall ensue, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) any moveable or immoveable property vested in him as such Agent shall become vested in his`
  line `successor in office, and`
  line
  line `(b) a suit or other proceeding instituted by his name of office may be continued by his successor in`
  line `office in the same manner as if the departure or the death, resignation or removal had not occurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
